{{Tibetan Buddhism}}
'''Dajyur''' or the Damxung Horse Festival is a [[Tibet]]an [[festival]] that takes place at the beginning of the eighth month of the [[lunar calendar]] (solar September) throughout southern [[Tibet]]. The festivities last for ten days with events such as [[horse racing]], bicycle riding contests, and rock-carrying competitions contributing to a time of merriment and celebration.

