{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2016}}

'''Kenneth McCarthy''' (born c. 1980),<ref name="upvoted">{{cite web|url= http://redditblog.com/2015/10/03/ken-m-interview-internet-troll|title= Tracking Down Ken M, One of the Internet's Most Accidentally Prolific Trolls|website= Upvoted|author= Natasha Umer|date= October 3, 2015}}</ref> popularly known as '''Ken M''', is an [[Internet troll]] known for his comments on news websites such as [[Yahoo!]] and ''[[The Huffington Post]]''. Unlike the more common associations for the term ''troll'' on the internet, Ken's comments are usually benign, with his comments displaying a complete lack of understanding of the featured topic, while other commenters take him seriously.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/2016/5/6/11597960/ken-m-internet-troll|title=The world's greatest internet troll explains his craft|last=Edwards|first=Phil|date=2016-05-06|work=[[Vox (website)]]|access-date=2018-05-17}}</ref>

Ken M worked as a [[copywriter]] for [[Comedy Central]] and a columnist for [[College Humor (magazine)|College Humor]]<ref name="upvoted" /> and started posting to [[comments sections]] as Ken M in 2011 on various websites, mostly [[Yahoo!]] and ''[[The Huffington Post]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://gizmodo.com/ken-m-is-the-most-epic-troll-on-the-internet-1739028329|title= Ken M Is The Most Epic Troll on the Internet|website= Gizmodo|author= Kaila Hale-Stern|date= October 28, 2015}}</ref> He has said that his aim was to "turn a toxic space into a source of belly laughter."<ref name="upvoted" /> His absurd comments over the years made him widely considered one of the most prolific Internet trolls ever,<ref name="upvoted" /><ref name="time">{{cite web|url= http://time.com/4258291/30-most-influential-people-on-the-internet-2016|title= The 30 Most Influential People on the Internet|website= Time|author= Samantha Grossman|date= March 16, 2016}}</ref> gaining thousands of fans on Facebook, Twitter, his [[Reddit|subreddit]], and [[Tumblr]] where he posts screenshots of all his comments as ''HorseySurprise''.<ref name="time" /><ref name="uproxx">{{cite web|url= http://uproxx.com/webculture/ken-m-yahoo-comment-trolling|title= Meet Ken M, The Rembrandt of Yahoo Comment Trolling|website= Uproxx|author= Caleb Reading|date= February 10, 2012}}</ref> Ken M was named one of the most influential people on the Internet by ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' in 2016<ref name="time" /> and 'The Rembrandt of Yahoo Comment Trolling' by [[Uproxx]].<ref name="uproxx" />

